n period. He explores at length the notions of primary versus secondary religions, of "counter-religions," and of book religions versus cultic religions. He also deals with the entry of ethics into religion's very core. Informed by the debate his own work has generated, he presents a compelling lesson in the fluidity of cultural identity and beliefs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aMonotheismxHistory. 0aPaganismxHistory. 0aReligion and culturexHistory. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh1 aSavage, Robert08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477286040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804772860423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804772860.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles